Reasoning: The paper discusses a method for fast approximation of sparse coding and its application to object classification, which are both topics related to computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves learning a dictionary and assignment of allowed dictionary elements, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of lookup tables and pseudoinverses, which are common in neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
